longBusinessSummary: Maheshwari Logistics Limited, together with its subsidiaries, provides logistics services in India. The company operates through four segments: Trade Division, Coal Division, Paper Division, and Waste Division. It offers logistics services for various industries, such as cement, paper, textiles, fertilizers, etc. The company also owns trucks. In addition, it is involved in trading and import of coal; dealing in petcoke, diesel, and waste paper products; manufacture of recycled kraft paper; and trading and exports of various papers. Maheshwari Logistics Limited was incorporated in 2006 and is headquartered in Vapi, India.
